parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of brakes in cold weather can lead to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Brakes do not work properly in cold weather
brake pedal goes to the floor
extended stopping distance
brakes malfunction at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration when braking can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, as the vehicle may lose control or collide with other objects.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped disc brakes can cause vibration, noise, and reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Warped disc brakes
vibration when braking
noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake component wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and accidents, posing a risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Excessive wear on brake rotors and pads
frequent replacement of brake components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Goes to the Floor with Grinding Noise
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A brake pedal that goes to the floor with a grinding noise can indicate a serious brake system failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
grinding noise when braking
brakes do not operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning shoulder belt can lead to inadequate restraint during an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The shoulder belt does not retract or adjust properly
causing discomfort or injury to the consumer
the belt gets stuck
the plastic piece sticks to the consumer's back and top of head
the belt does not provide adequate support.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of motor belts can cause engine damage, overheating, or failure, leading to costly repairs, loss of vehicle function, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Motor belts fail to operate
belts break or crack
engine damage or overheating occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and breakage of the brake wire bracket can cause the anti-lock brake electrical wire to chafe and fail, leading to potential brake system failure and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake wire is exposed and rubbing against other wheel assembly components
the brake wire insulation is damaged
the brake system may malfunction or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Child Safety Seat Tether Strap Anchorage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a suitable tether strap anchorage point can compromise the safety of child passengers in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Difficulty or impossibility of securely installing child safety seats that require a tether strap
increased risk of child injury or fatality in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leakage into the passenger compartment can cause discomfort, distraction, and potentially lead to electrical system malfunctions or other safety issues.
symptoms: Water drips or leaks into the passenger compartment
water accumulates on surfaces or floors
occupants may experience discomfort or distraction due to water leakage.
